config IEEE80211_ASSERT
	int
	default 2
	help
	Set the verbosity level of KASSERT() and assert() function.
	 0: the assert() macro generates no code, and hence does nothing at all.
	    Set this level only if you are sure that your module is mature enough.
	 1: the assert() macro causes the system to generate a trap if the condition
	    is evaluated to be false, but does not print the file, line, function
	    information.
	 2: the assert() macro, on false conditions, prints out detailed information
	    and then causes the trap. This is the default.

